J. H. BERLING DAIRY PRODUCTS CO., J. H. Berling, A. H. Berling and L. H. Smart, v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 8283. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Jan. 16, 1940. Sanford A. Headley and Michael C. Lacinak, both of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellant. Leo Calvin Crawford, U. S. Atty., and Frederic W. Johnson, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS and SIMONS, - Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of the appellant, the appellee not objecting, it is now ordered that this cause, United States v. Krechting, D. C., 26 F.Supp. 266, be and the same is dismissed.
